<section class="tagline-section reveal" id="philosophy">
<div class="tagline-eyebrow">Architectural Principle</div>
<div class="tagline-text">The entrance shapes the arrival. A visitor who arrives at The Prayers through "Holding Cell with a Bench and a Drain" has a different experience than one who arrives through "Natural Built Then Ruined or Softened Shelter."</div>
<div class="tagline-sub">Sixty percent outdoors. The word "grounds" was chosen because the practice is experienced more outdoors than in. Canyon basins, salt flats, peat bogs, mesa tops, fjords, limestone bluffs, river deltas. The vocabulary reflects where the work actually lives.</div>
</section>

